// scenarios/69-jenkins-library-mutable-ref
// CICD-SEC-3 (Dependency Chain Abuse) — Jenkins
//
// Pattern: a shared library loaded via `@Library('lib@master')` — a MUTABLE
// branch ref. Whoever can push to that library repo's `master` executes code in
// every consuming pipeline on the next run. (A *trusted*, folder-global library
// runs outside the Groovy sandbox, making it controller RCE.) Jenkins analogue
// of the mutable-action-ref / reusable-workflow-trust class (scenarios 03 / 28).
//
// SAFETY: static fixture, nested under scenarios/ (Jenkins runs only a
// configured Jenkinsfile). See README.md.

// DANGER — mutable branch ref. Pin to an immutable tag or commit SHA instead.
@Library('platform-shared-lib@master') _

pipeline {
    agent { label 'build-linux' }
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                buildUtils.compile()   // provided by the mutable shared library
            }
        }
    }
}
